						               													<description>Business 2000 is a board game you can play with the whole family or with friends. The game was first released in 1989. The rules of the game are very similar to the well-known series of Monopoly board games . Therefore, a person who had ever played Monopoly, will quickly adapt to the rules of Business 2000.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Business 2000 is an economic strategy that contributes to the development of logic and observation, responsibility for decision making and ability to predict results.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is a roll-and-move game, where the participants throw the dice and walk around the perimeter of the playing field. They buy or sell various properties, companies and even entire industries. The players can also develop their property.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players have the right to trade and negotiate with each other at any time. The ultimate goal is to drive opponents into bankruptcy. The main differences from the Monopoly series are special fields and action cards, that have specific rules, namely the &amp;quot;Casino&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Hippodrome&amp;quot; fields and the &amp;quot;Shares&amp;quot; special action cards, that increase a player's income every turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
